Timing of Benefit Payments  If a Participant is a key employee (as defined in Section 416(i) of the Code without regard to paragraph (5) thereof) and the Company's stock is publicly traded on an established securities market or otherwise, payment of the benefit hereunder shall be made no sooner than the beginning of the seventh month after the date of the Participant's separation from service unless the Participant has elected to receive payment as of a date certain in accordance with Section 4.6.  If a Participant is not described in the previous sentence, payment of his benefit shall be made or shall begin within 90 days following his termination of employment, unless the Participant has elected to receive payment as of a date in accordance with Section 4.6.
