Section 2.1
                                     
Formation of, and Contributions to, Newco
.  Prior to Closing, Seller shall cause Newco Parent to form Newco.  Immediately prior to Closing, Seller shall () cause the Contributing Entities to contribute to Newco all of the Contributing Entities' right, title, and interest in and to the Transferred Assets, free and clear of all liens other than Permitted Liens, and () cause Newco to assume the Assumed Liabilities.  All contributions of assets to, or assumptions of liability by, Newco shall be made pursuant to documents of transfer, assignment and contribution or assumption reasonably satisfactory to Purchaser.
