Federal and state deferred tax expense for the Successor period of 2009 increased compared to the Predecessor II period of 2008 due to bonus tax depreciation taken on fixed assets placed in service subsequent to January 9, 2009, as well as the reductions in property, plant and equipment and amortizable intangible assets resulting from the push-down of VZW's post-acquisition basis in the Markets, as further discussed in Note 3.  Current and deferred income taxes for the Predecessor II period of 2008 reflect timing differences between the amounts recorded in the financial statements and reported for income tax purposes primarily related to depreciation and amortization expense.  The timing differences include the effects of purchase accounting adjustments allocated to the Markets' tangible and intangible assets, as further discussed in Note 4.
