.  The representations and warranties of Sellers and Purchaser contained in this Agreement shall survive the Closing for the period set forth in this .  All representations and warranties contained in this Agreement and all claims with respect thereto shall terminate upon the expiration of eighteen (18) months after the Closing Date, except that () the representations and warranties contained in (FCC Matters) shall terminate upon the expiration of forty-eight (48) months after the Closing Date, () the representations and warranties contained in (Contracts) shall survive until the Alternative Agreement Termination Date  and () the representations and warranties contained in (Corporate Status), (Authorization; etc.), the third sentence of (Sufficiency) (Tax Matters), (Finders Fees), (Corporate Status), (Authorization; etc.), and (Finders Fees) shall survive until the expiration of the applicable statute of limitations, giving effect to any extensions thereof; , that in the event notice of any claim for indemnification under or has been given (within the meaning of ) within the applicable survival period, the representations and warranties that are the subject of such indemnification claim shall survive with respect to such claim until such time as such claim is finally resolved under the terms of this Agreement. The covenants and agreements of the parties contained in this Agreement or the Ancillary Agreements, or in connection herewith or therewith, shall survive the Closing indefinitely or until expiration of the relevant statute of limitation or, if a shorter period is explicitly specified herein or therein, for such shorter period.
